    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in France (
                        Caffery
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v05</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d77</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">77</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-09-26T06:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-09-26T06:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-26T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-26T06:00:00-05:00" n="77" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862R.014/9–2646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-26T12:00:00+01:00">September 26, 1946—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 9:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4819. Department’s 5049, September 24.<note n="10" xml:id="d77fn10">Not
                        printed.</note> We explained to Chauvel<note n="11" xml:id="d77fn11">Jean
                        Chauvel, Secretary General of the French Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</note>
                    the U.S. attitude regarding proposed annexation Southwest Africa which Union has
                    placed on <gloss target="#t_UNO1">UNO</gloss> agenda. He replied that our
                    proposal would have to be studied before he could give us an official reply but
                    to him personally it appeared “very reasonable”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
